<doc>
  <member name="D3D11_RAISE_FLAG">
    <summary>
      <para>Option(s) for raising an error to a non-continuable exception.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>These flags are used by <see cref="ID3D11Device.GetExceptionMode" /> and <see cref="ID3D11Device.SetExceptionMode" />. Use 0 to indicate no flags; multiple flags can be logically OR'ed together.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d11/d3d11-graphics-reference-d3d11-core-enums">Core Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_RAISE_FLAG.D3D11_RAISE_FLAG_DRIVER_INTERNAL_ERROR">
    <summary>
      <para>Raise an internal driver error to a non-continuable exception.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>